# Frontend Architecture

## Layer Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│        Presentation Layer           │
│     (Components, Views, UI)         │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│       Application Layer             │
│  (State Management, Routing, Hooks) │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│         Domain Layer                │
│   (Business Logic, Entities)        │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│      Infrastructure Layer           │
│    (API, Storage, Services)         │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Keep each layer ignorant of layers above it. Domain and Infrastructure layers must never import React.

## Component Design

### Core Rules
- **Single Responsibility**: one clear purpose per component
- **Composition over inheritance**: compose with props/children, not class extension
- **Container vs Presentational**: split data-fetching logic from rendering

```tsx
// Presentational — pure UI, no data fetching
function UserCard({ user, onEdit, onDelete }: UserCardProps) { ... }

// Container — owns data and callbacks, delegates rendering
function UserCardContainer({ userId }: { userId: string }) {
  const { data: user } = useQuery(['user', userId], () => fetchUser(userId));
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  return <UserCard user={user} onEdit={() => navigate(`/users/${userId}/edit`)} ... />;
}
```

## State Management Decision Guide

| State Type | Tool | When |
|---|---|---|
| UI-only (open/closed, input value) | `useState` | Component-local, not shared |
| Shared between siblings | Lift to parent | Sibling components need the same value |
| App-wide (auth, theme) | Context + `useReducer` | Infrequently-changing global state |
| Server/async data | React Query / SWR | Anything fetched from an API |
| Complex client state | Zustand or Jotai | Large client-side state, devtools needed |

### Unidirectional Flow (always)
Action → Reducer → State → View → Action

Never mutate state directly. Use immutable updates (`{ ...state, key: value }`).

## Design Patterns Quick Reference

| Pattern | Best For |
|---|---|
| **MVC** | Classic separation; models with observer subscriptions |
| **MVVM** | Computed/derived UI state; ViewModel as mediator |
| **Flux** | Unidirectional data with central dispatcher and stores |
| **Observer** | Real-time updates (WebSocket, presence, feeds) |
| **Factory** | Dynamic component/form creation from schemas |
| **Module (IIFE)** | Encapsulating private state with a public API |

For full implementations, see the companion rules `frontend-architecture-patterns` and `frontend-architecture-build-testing`.

## Folder Structure

```
src/
├── features/           # Feature-based slices
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   ├── hooks/
│   │   ├── services/
│   │   ├── types/
│   │   └── index.ts    # Public API of the feature
│   ├── products/
│   └── cart/
├── shared/             # Cross-feature UI and utilities
│   ├── components/
│   ├── hooks/
│   └── utils/
├── core/               # App infrastructure
│   ├── api/
│   ├── router/
│   └── store/
└── pages/              # Route-level containers
```

### Naming Conventions
| Kind | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Components | PascalCase | `UserProfile.tsx` |
| Hooks | `use` prefix, camelCase | `useAuth.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `formatDate.ts` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_FILE_SIZE` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `UserRole`, `CartItem` |
| Test files | same name + `.test` | `UserCard.test.tsx` |

## Module Systems

### Code Splitting
```tsx
// Route-based (preferred default)
const Dashboard = lazy(() => import('./pages/Dashboard'));

// Wrap all lazy routes
<Suspense fallback={<PageLoader />}>
  <Routes>...</Routes>
</Suspense>
```

### Tree Shaking
```ts
// Good — named imports
import { debounce } from 'lodash-es';

// Bad — imports entire bundle
import _ from 'lodash';
```

Mark `sideEffects: ["*.css"]` in `package.json` to enable aggressive tree shaking.

## Build Tools

### Vite (recommended)
```ts
// vite.config.ts
build: {
  rollupOptions: {
    output: {
      manualChunks: {
        'react-vendor': ['react', 'react-dom', 'react-router-dom'],
        'utils': ['date-fns', 'lodash-es']
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Webpack
Use `splitChunks` with `cacheGroups` to separate vendor and common chunks. Set `contenthash` in output filenames for long-term caching.

## Testing Pyramid

```
        /\
       /E2E\          ← Few, full user flows (Playwright)
      /──────\
     /Integr. \       ← Component + hook interactions
    /──────────\
   /   Unit    \      ← Functions, isolated components (Jest + RTL)
  /────────────\
```

### Test Utility Pattern
Always wrap renders with providers:
```tsx
function renderWithProviders(ui, { preloadedState } = {}) {
  return render(ui, { wrapper: ({ children }) => (
    <Provider store={store}>
      <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
        <BrowserRouter>{children}</BrowserRouter>
      </QueryClientProvider>
    </Provider>
  )});
}
```

Use factory functions for test data:
```ts
function createMockUser(overrides?: Partial<User>): User {
  return { id: '1', email: 'test@example.com', name: 'Test User', role: 'user', ...overrides };
}
```

## Performance Checklist

- [ ] Route-based code splitting with `lazy()` + `Suspense`
- [ ] Named imports from tree-shakeable libraries
- [ ] `manualChunks` separating vendor from app code
- [ ] `contenthash` in output filenames for cache busting
- [ ] React Query `staleTime` configured (avoid over-fetching)
- [ ] Images use `loading="lazy"` and IntersectionObserver
- [ ] Infinite lists use `useInfiniteQuery` + sentinel element
- [ ] Service Worker caches static assets

## Architecture Checklist

- [ ] Each layer only depends on layers below it
- [ ] Domain and infra layers have zero React imports
- [ ] Components follow single responsibility
- [ ] State is at the correct level (local → lifted → global → server)
- [ ] Unidirectional data flow enforced (no circular updates)
- [ ] Feature folders export a single `index.ts` public API
- [ ] Naming conventions applied consistently
- [ ] Tests exist at all three pyramid levels
- [ ] Bundle analyzed for unexpected large chunks
